column1: #Text=, is a city located in Pakistan ' s Punjab province .
#Text=It is a mid-country city located at the junction of all four provinces of Pakistan .
#Text=The city also gives its name to the Dera Ghazi Khan Division , which consists of the Dera Ghazi Khan , Rajanpur , Muzaffargarh and Layyah districts .
#Text=It is also the capital of Dera Ghazi Khan District
#Text=Dera Ghazi Khan International Airport is over 15 kilometres from the city .
#Text=Pakistan 's flag carrier PIA operates here directly from Karachi , Lahore , Islamabad , Quetta , Bahawalpur , Dubai and Jeddah .
#Text=Shaheen Air and Air Indus also operate here from Karachi .
#Text=Khushhal Khan Khattak Express , a daily express train service between Karachi and Peshawar briefly stop at Dera Ghazi Khan Cantt .
#Text=The city is well connected with whole country by road .
#Text=Daewoo , Faisal Movers , Baloch , Ghazi and Adil Shah are the buses which connect Dera Ghazi Khan to other major cities .
#Text=Auto-rickshaws / tuk-tuks are open rickshaws with ( narrow ) rear-facing seats , or with two seats facing forward and two backward .
#Text=They are handy for moving around in the Inner City , since it 's easier to see where you 're going .
#Text=Try to find a rickshaw with a well-padded seat , otherwise you will come out bruised and aching .

#Text=A beautiful hill station , located at a height of 6,470 feet above sea level located around 80 kilometres west ward from Dera Ghazi Khan city , is a cool resort in summers for the people living in Southern part of Punjab .
#Text=This hill station is part of the Sulaiman Mountain range , attracts many visitors for short stays during the season of summer to enjoy mild and pleasant weather for a day or two .
#Text=, Village Muqam ( 35 kilometres from Dera Ghazi Khan city ) .
#Text=Tomb of Hazrat Sakhi Sarwar Syed Ahmed Sultan , built in the 13th century is a unique building of Mughal architecture .
#Text=Thousands of people from all over the Subcontinent come here on the Annual Celebrations of Birth of Sakhi Sarwar in March every year .
#Text=Many people speak Saraiki and some people speak Urdu
